dential spatial order in order to theorize diaspora space, in the context of the Roma Diaspora. This work will offer readers new possibilities to re-imagine diaspora through law and literature and provides an innovative critical interdisciplinary analysis of the shaping of space.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2019) 4aCritical Legal Theory. 4aRoma Diaspora. 4aSpace. 4aTextual Criticism. 70(DE-601)1049772640(DE-588)4225698-7aRaumgMotiv2gnd 70(DE-601)1061819550(DE-588)4050473-6aRomagVolk2gnd 70(DE-601)1062450150(DE-588)4035964-5aLiteratur2gnd 70(DE-601)3264321400(DE-588)4619771-0aDiasporagMotiv2gnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2016-2019z978311063851608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831105436980 cprintz978311054363640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110544251423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110544251.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-063851-6  DG and UP eBook Package 2016-2019c2016d2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DKUb2017